HEADWORD: hard-pressed
<hw>hard-pressed</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>facing or experiencing
trouble or difficulty; <as>as, financially <ex>hard-pressed</ex> Mexican
hotels are lowering their prices; they were <ex>hard-pressed</ex> to
find a substitute on short notice</as>; -- see
<er>distressed</er>{1}.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> distressed, hard put, in a bad way(predicate), in
trouble(predicate).</syn>⟦br⟧
